Description: Head and necks of two bulls, conjoined; above, triskeles (?). (obverse)
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Town (Naukratis), Silversmith's Hoard (IGCH 1647), eastern part of town
Curator's comments: From the 'Silversmith's Hoard'; see Petrie's Journal 1884-5,139, where he states it was found casually and that he visited the site, but does not specify the location.
Bibliographic references: BMC Greek (Lycia, Pamphylia) / Catalogue of the Greek coins of Lycia, Pamphylia and Pisidia (71, p.15) (wrongly said to have been found by Petrie (B.V. Head in Petrie 1886, 64))
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (UA.026)
